                <p>The Secretary of the Army proposes to meet the request for a mechanized brigade
                    by deploying a brigade from the 5th Mechanized Division. He now believes it
                    cannot be ready to deploy before 12 July.</p>
                <pb facs="0427" n="383" xml:id="pg_383"/>
                <p>Moreover, for the reasons noted earlier, I would like to substitute an Army
                    infantry brigade and support personnel for the 27th Regimental Landing Team and
                    support personnel that deployed in February. Therefore, I would propose to
                    substitute 7,363 Army personnel for Marines in the first half of July. The Army
                    can provide the personnel; the Secretary of the Navy now believes the 27th
                        <gloss target="#t_RLT1">RLT</gloss> can be sustained until then.<note n="2"
                        xml:id="d127fn2">In a March 14 memorandum to <persName corresp="#p_NP1"
                            >Nitze</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_RS1">Resor</persName> noted
                        that the replacement would require an additional call-up of units with
                        13,500 personnel and a corresponding increase in the <gloss
                            target="#t_MACV1">MACV</gloss> ceiling. (Ibid.)</note>
                </p>
                <p>Would you please inform General <persName corresp="#p_WGWC1"
                        >Westmoreland</persName> of these proposals, and of my preference for them,
                    and ask him whether he considers the substitutions satisfactory.<note n="3"
                        xml:id="d127fn3">In a March 14 memorandum to <persName corresp="#p_NP1"
                            >Nitze</persName>, <persName corresp="#p_WGE1">Wheeler</persName> noted
                        that he would inform <persName corresp="#p_WGWC1">Westmoreland</persName> of
                        the substitute package. In addition, he inquired whether his understanding
                        that reserve units and individual reservists would be called-up but terms of
                        service would not be extended was correct. <persName corresp="#p_NP1"
                            >Nitze</persName> indicated “no” on the memorandum and wrote: “Would
                        like to know what we are going to do, of course.” (Ibid.)</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>Paul H. Nitze </signed>
                </closer>
